The Nigeria Police Force on Friday said salary short-payment for personnel for the month of April, 2018 is being resolved, with the office of the Accountant-General of the Federation. Spokesman, ACP Jimoh Moshood, said it was due to a system error, and is being promptly resolved. “The affected personnel will according to OAGF get the salary differential paid on or before Monday, May 7th, 2018,” he added.